  "conclusion": "Spirometry was attempted but was technically inadequate. Patient (age 4 years 2 months) was unable to perform a reproducible forced expiratory maneuver. Could not sustain exhalation for the minimum acceptable duration. Flow-volume loops were not reproducible across 6 attempts. Test documented as not interpretable. Will be reattempted at next visit when patient is older and more cooperative."
